_properties.descriptionZh: 边界框是由两个点形成的矩形所包围的区域。第一个点是下角，第二个点是上角。边界框用空格符分隔的两个点来表示。
_properties.rdfs:comment: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.
_properties.rdfs:label: box

_properties.descriptionZh: 圆是以某个指定经维度为中心指定长度为半径的区域。圆是由一对坐标加上以米为单位的半径来表示的。
_properties.rdfs:comment: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.
_properties.rdfs:label: circle

_properties.descriptionZh: 由两点或多点组成的点对点路径
_properties.rdfs:comment: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.
_properties.rdfs:label: line

_properties.descriptionZh: 多边形是由起点和终点相同的点对点路径包围的区域。 多边形表示为一系列四个或更多的空格分隔点，其中第一个和最后一个点相同。
_properties.rdfs:comment: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.
_properties.rdfs:label: polygon

_properties.descriptionZh: 该项的一个附加类型， 通常用于从外部词典中向微数据语法添加更加具体的类型。它表示事物和事物本身所属的类之间的关系。在RDFa语法中, 对多类型最好使用‘typeof’属性这样的本地RDFa语法. Schema.org 工具对额外类型的理解较弱，特别是外部定义的额外类型。
_properties.rdfs:comment: An additional type for the item, typically used for adding more specific types from external vocabularies in microdata syntax. This is a relationship between something and a class that the thing is in. In RDFa syntax, it is better to use the native RDFa syntax - the 'typeof' attribute - for multiple types. Schema.org tools may have only weaker understanding of extra types, in particular those defined externally.
_properties.rdfs:label: additionalType

  bread.

  Cook time: 1 hour
  Yield: 1 loaf
  Tags: Low fat
  
    Nutrition facts:
    240 calories,
    9 grams fat
  
  Ingredients:
  - 3 or 4 ripe bananas, smashed
  - 1 egg
  - 3/4 cup of sugar
  ...

  Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Mix in the ingredients in a bowl. Add
  the flour last. Pour the mixture into a loaf pan and bake for one hour.

isDomainOf.rdfs:comment: The country. For example, USA. You can also provide the two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code.
isDomainOf.rdfs:label: addressCountry

isDomainOf.descriptionZh: 边界框是由两个点形成的矩形所包围的区域。第一个点是下角，第二个点是上角。边界框用空格符分隔的两个点来表示。
isDomainOf.rdfs:comment: A box is the area enclosed by the rectangle formed by two points. The first point is the lower corner, the second point is the upper corner. A box is expressed as two points separated by a space character.
isDomainOf.rdfs:label: box

isDomainOf.descriptionZh: 圆是以某个指定经维度为中心指定长度为半径的区域。圆是由一对坐标加上以米为单位的半径来表示的。
isDomainOf.rdfs:comment: A circle is the circular region of a specified radius centered at a specified latitude and longitude. A circle is expressed as a pair followed by a radius in meters.
isDomainOf.rdfs:label: circle

isDomainOf.descriptionZh: 由两点或多点组成的点对点路径
isDomainOf.rdfs:comment: A line is a point-to-point path consisting of two or more points. A line is expressed as a series of two or more point objects separated by space.
isDomainOf.rdfs:label: line

isDomainOf.descriptionZh: 多边形是由起点和终点相同的点对点路径包围的区域。 多边形表示为一系列四个或更多的空格分隔点，其中第一个和最后一个点相同。
isDomainOf.rdfs:comment: A polygon is the area enclosed by a point-to-point path for which the starting and ending points are the same. A polygon is expressed as a series of four or more space delimited points where the first and final points are identical.
isDomainOf.rdfs:label: polygon
